He is member for the Samoa national team and currently national captain.Tim Cahill, Football (soccer)\nHe played in the 2010 FIFA World Cup Qualifiers, scoring goals against Vanuatu, Rivals American Samoa and Tonga and he is currently Injured due to Club Football duties which means he won't appear for his Nation at the 2012 OFC Oceania Cup in the Solomon Islands which is Samoa's first ever appearance at a Football Major Tournament.